[[div class="bulletin"]]

**Site-19 Bulletin Board - 05/01/2024**

[[div class="bulletin-entry"]]

**SCP-451**

Junior Researcher Terry Choyce
----

Hey everyone,

I've recently discovered a possible method to help out [[[SCP-451]]].
I would be grateful if someone more familiar with his circumstances could collab with me, and draft up an experiment plan.
Please see the database entry for [[span style="color:blue"]] SCP-XXXX [[/span]] and reach out to either myself or Researcher Cartwright.

[[/div]]

[[/div]]


[[div class="experiment"]]
**Researcher(s)**: Snr. Researcher A. Cartwright, Jnr. Researcher T. Choyce
**Subject(s)**:  D-0850, D-3131
**Procedure**: D-0850 wears SCP-XXXX-A. D-0850 is exposed to a visual Class II Foundation cognitohazard.
D-3131 watches SCP-XXXX-B placed at a distance of 1m from D-0850.
----
**Results**: D-0850 coughs and expels approximately 20ml of blood. D-3131 experiences a nosebleed.
[[/div]]


[[div class="experiment"]]
**Researcher(s)**: Jnr. Researcher T. Choyce
**Subject(s)**: D-4450, --D-2294,-- D-3399[[footnote]] D-3399 is scheduled on death row.[[/footnote]], 
**Procedure**: D-3399 wears SCP-XXXX-A. D-3399 is exposed to --a visual-- an auditory Class --II-- V Foundation cognitohazard.
D-4450 watches SCP-XXXX-B placed at a distance of --5m-- 65m.
--**Status**: Auto-rejected. Staff on disciplinary probation require a supervising researcher.--
**Status**: Approved -  Snr. Researcher A. Cartwright

**Addendum XXXX.8:** Initial proposed procedure is unlikely to yield new insights. - //Cartwright//
**Addendum XXXX.9:** Also, why didn't you tell me that you're on probation?! - //Cartwright//
----
**Results**: D-3399 expires.
--SCP-XXXX-B displays television static-- The melody of the cognitohazard is barely intelligible from SCP-XXXX-B.
D-4450 --appears OK-- suffers from a migraine lasting 30s.
**Addendum XXXX.10:** The cognitive suppression effect appears to be inversely proportional to the audiovisual resolution of the feed produced by SCP-XXXX-B - //Cartwright//
[[/div]]

[[div class="experiment"]]
**Researcher(s)**: Snr. Researcher A. Cartwright, Jnr. Researcher T. Choyce
**Subject(s)**:  D-0850, D-3131
**Procedure**: D-0850 is exposed to a visual Class II Foundation cognitohazard.
D-3131 is exposed to the same visual Class II Foundation cognitohazard, overlayed with television static to obfuscate the cognitohazard to be barely legible.
----
**Results**: D-0850 coughs and expels approximately 20ml of blood. D-3131 inspects the television static, and coughs 20ml of blood upon discerning the cognitohazard.
**Addendum XXXX.11:** Verifies that our Foundation cognitohazards can't be circumvented by non-anomalous TV static.
[[/div]]

[[collapsible show="**LEVEL 4 CLEARANCE REQUIRED" hide="- Hide"]]
[[div class="experiment"]]
**Researcher(s)**: Jnr. Researcher T. Choyce
**Subject(s)**:  D-1142, [[[SCP-2521|●●|●●●●●|●●|●]]]
**Procedure**: D-1142 wears SCP-XXXX-A and looks at a photograph of numbers representing ●●|●●●●●|●●|●.
